{
  "stem": "21004.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "My zayde, he had a mill, you know, to-- to make flour by hand, a round one, because usually when we have a lot, we used to go to the-- to one place where they have a big mill, you know.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But this, for Pesach, he used to cut out the stone, make it really for Pesach.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Cut out the chisel, cut out, clean it out, and then make it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And he also gave to the rabbis in Krakowice and Jaworow, not to every-- every rabbi wouldn't take it, but from my grandfather, from my mother, whatever we brought them, they were happy.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We brought them the flour and they were making the matzohs, very, very strict, strict, really strict.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "So-- And the holidays were really nice.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "The holidays, everybody was really nice, enjoyable, family together.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH] bringing presents, gifts, all kind of holidays.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, this was already starting like 1930, '33 when Hitler came to power.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they start putting out young boys, Ukrainian boys and also in Poland was the same thing, putting on placards putting on [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Hit the Jew, kill him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "A Jew is a pig, [NON-ENGLISH], all kind terrible things.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then making swastikas, making on the walls.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Nobody did it by us, because they respected my mother on account of the parents.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This is the younger generation did it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But it started getting bad, so everybody was thinking to go out, so I used to go to look first in Lemberg, to a big city, to find a job in the city.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Well, find a good job, and I had where to stay by a cousin.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And she had a fur-- a fur.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they were dealing with furs.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They had a beautiful story in Lwow.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
